<h1 align="center"><b>Milton "Bill" Finger</h1>
<h2 align="center">The Co-Creator of the Caped Crusader</b></h2>
<p align="center"><img alt="Bill_Finger_Image" class='biggerImage' src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/09/Bill_finger_photo.jpg" >
</p>
<p></p>

<p>Bill Finger was a writer for <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/DC_Comics' target=blank>DC Comics</a>, and is now recognized as the co-creator of the  super hero character: <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batman' target=blank><b>Batman</b></a>. DC Comics artist <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Kane' target=blank><b>Bob Kane</b></a> <a href='http://www.followingthenerd.com/site/wp-content/uploads/bob-kane-batman-before-bill-finger.jpg' target=blank>created the original artistic design for Batman</a>, but Bill came up with Batman's modern design that he's known for. The white-eyes aspect was inspired by comic strip writer <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lee_Falk' target=blank>Lee Falk's  <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phantom_(comics)' target=blank><b>The Phantom</b></a>, and the detective-personality was inspried by <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sherlock_Holmes' target=blank>Sherlock Holmes</a>.

Bill was primarily a writer for DC, the character and setting of <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gotham_City' target=blank><b>Gotham City</b></a>. Bill was uncredited for decades for his contributions, due to a contract Bob had with DC Comics. This led the public to believe Bob Kane was the sole creator of Batman. Bill’s legacy came to light thanks in part to Mark Tyler Noble’s book <a href='https://www.amazon.com/Bill-Boy-Wonder-Secret-Co-Creator/dp/1580892892' target=blank>Bill the Boy Wonder: The Secret Co-Creator of Batman</a>.</p>



<b>History</b>
  
<p><ol><b>1914</b> – Born on February 8 in Denver, Colorado</ol>

<ol><b>1939</b> – Co-Created and wrote the comic book character <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batman' target=blank><b>Batman</b></a> with <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bob_Kane' target=blank>Bob Kane</a> in <a href='http://dc.wikia.com/wiki/Detective_Comics_Vol_1_27' target=blank>Detective Comics #27</a></ol>

<ol><b>1940</b> – Co-created and wrote the comic book character <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dick_Grayson' target=blank><b>Robin</b> (Dick Grayson)</a>, Batman's sideick, with Bob Kane and <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jerry_Robinson'>Jerry Robinson</a> in <a href='http://dc.wikia.com/wiki/Detective_Comics_Vol_1_38' target=blank>Detective Comics #38</a></ol> 

<ol><b>1940</b> – Co-created and wrote the comic book character <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clayface'><b>Clayface</b></a> with Bob Kane in <a href='http://dc.wikia.com/wiki/Detective_Comics_Vol_1_40' target=blank>Detective Comics #40</a></ol>

<ol><b>1940</b> – Co-created and wrote the comic book character <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joker_(comics)' target=blank><b>the Joker</b></a> with Bob Kane and Jerry Robinson</a> in <a href='http://batman.wikia.com/wiki/Batman_Issue_1' target=blank>Batman #1</a></ol>

<ol><b>1940</b> - Co-created and wrote the comic book character <a href 'https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Scott' target=blank><b>The Green Lantern</b> (Alan Scott)</a> with <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Martin_Nodell' target=blank>Martin Nodell</a> in <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/All-American_Comics' target=blank>All-American Comics #16</a></ol>

<ol><b>1940</b> - Co-created and wrote the fictional comic book setting of <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gotham_City' target=blank>"New York City" (later <b>Gotham City</b>)</a> in <a href='http://batman.wikia.com/wiki/Batman_Issue_4'>Batman #4</a></ol>

<ol><b>1950</b> – Co-created and wrote comic book character<a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lana_Lang' target=blank> <b>Lana Lang</b></a> with <a href='http://www.dccomics.com/talent/john-sikela' target=blank>John Sikela</a> in <a href='http://dc.wikia.com/wiki/Superboy_Vol_1_10' target=blank>Superboy #10</a></ol>


<ol><b>1974</b> – dies at the age of 59</ol></p>
<p></p>

<p><ol><b>1999</b> – inducted into <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Eisner_Award_winners' target=blank><b>The Will Eisner Award Hall of Fame</b> by judges' choice</a></ol>

<ol><b>2005</b> - <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bill_Finger_Award' target=blank><b>The Bill Finger Award For Excellence In Comic Book Writing</b></a> is founded by Jerry Robinson<ol></p>
  
<ol><b>2015</b> - Bill Finger receives official credit as co-creator of Batman starting with the film <a href="http://www.imdb.com/title/tt2975590/"><b>Batman V Superman: Dawn of Justice</b></a> and television show <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gotham_(TV_series)'><b>Gotham</b>(Season 2 onward)</a>

